cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.SDQ 

The paper deals with automatic speech recognition (ASR) using neural networks and beamforming techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SD (Sound), which deals with audio and speech processing. The paper also involves the use of neural networks for mask estimation, which falls under the category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the optimization of the beamforming operation, which can be related to optimization techniques in machine learning, and hence cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. The paper also involves signal processing techniques, which can be related to cs.SI (Signal Processing) and cs.SDQ (Sound and Quality).
